headlines.description: — Mo Bamba had 22 points and 15 rebounds — both career highs — and the Orlando Magic beat the Detroit Pistons 119-112 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic top Pistons 119-112 behind Bamba's big night

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had the third game in NBA history with 20-plus rebounds and 20-plus assists — he and Wilt Chamberlain have the other two — and the surging Washington Wizards moved closer to Indiana in the Eastern Conference playoff standings by...
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook has 21 boards, 24 assists; Wizards blast Pacers

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 41 points, Draymond Green had 10 points, 15 assists and 13 rebounds, and the Golden State Warriors took a big step toward locking up a postseason berth with a 123-108 victory over the desperate New Orleans Pelicans on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry's 41 points push Warriors past Pelicans 123-108

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Danilo Gallinari made seven 3-pointers and finished with 28 points, leading the Atlanta Hawks to a 123-114 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers in a matchup Monday night of teams battling for playoff positioning in their respective conferences.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gallinari, Bogdanovic lead Hawks past Trail Blazers 123-114

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris scored 21 points, Seth Curry added 20 and the Philadelphia 76ers won their fifth straight game, beating the Chicago Bulls 106-94 on Monday night.

events.name: New York Knicks at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Julius Randle scored 28 points, Derrick Rose added 25, converting 11 of 15 shots and the New York Knicks held off the Memphis Grizzlies 118-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle, Rose lead Knicks to win over Grizzlies

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 25 points and Rudy Gobert tallied 24 points and 15 rebounds to help the Utah Jazz beat the San Antonio Spurs 110-99 on Monday night.

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored 25 points and had key plays on both ends of the floor in the final minute as the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers snapped a three-game losing streak with a 93-89 victory over the Denver Nuggets Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores 25 as short-handed Lakers defeat Nuggets 93-89
